01:09:51.590 --> 01:09:54.270
I mixed a Jeff Babko
record last year--

01:09:54.270 --> 01:09:56.435
those end up being much quieter
mixes, because I want

01:09:56.435 --> 01:09:58.340
it to be more open, and
the dynamic range

01:09:58.340 --> 01:09:59.360
really helps the music.

01:09:59.360 --> 01:10:01.140
So for me, it's much
more a feel thing.

01:10:01.140 --> 01:10:03.200
And then I find out later that
I've kind of screwed up, and

01:10:03.200 --> 01:10:04.820
the mastering guy gets angry.

01:10:04.820 --> 01:10:07.440
And then I will send the quieter
makes and say, if you

01:10:07.440 --> 01:10:10.580
